es that the answer won=E2=80=99t be as straightforward as you=E2=80=99d thi=
nk. Think of puns, wordplay, homonyms, and less-obvious answers.</li><li><s=
trong class=3D"prismic-strong">Tenses in clues are written to match the ans=
wers.</strong>&nbsp;If you=E2=80=99re searching for crossword synonyms, sti=
ck to the same past, future, or present tense that the clue is in. For inst=
ance, the clue =E2=80=9Cjumped=E2=80=9D would not result in =E2=80=9Chops=
=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Chopping=E2=80=9D but =E2=80=9Chopped.=E2=80=9D</li><l=
i><strong class=3D"prismic-strong">Consider abbreviations carefully.</stron=
g>&nbsp;If a clue is abbreviated, the answer will likely be, too. Memorize =
